 directed its music video, in which Rihanna\'s character shoots a man after he rapes her. The video was criticized by the Parents Television Council, Industry Ears and Mothers Against Violence, who faulted Rihanna for suggesting that murder is an acceptable form of justice for rape victims. However, actress Gabrielle Union, a rape victim, praised the video for being relatable. \"Man Down\" was on the set list for three of Rihanna\'s tours – the Loud Tour (2011), the Diamonds World Tour (2013) and the Anti World Tour (2016).', NULL),
